description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to appoint Nurses and Paramedics to expand the clinical teams based in our Bristol and Exeter Clinical Hubs (999 control rooms).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Clinicians provide primary clinical triage to patients, making interventions across the whole spectrum of health and social care to direct callers to the most appropriate care. They also provide advice and assistance to Clinical Hub staff and managers as required, whilst ensuring the safe and effective delivery of our emergency and urgent care service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be a registered Paramedic or Nurse with a broad general experience as a qualified professional. You must have a wider knowledge of healthcare pathways, and have experience in triaging patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This can be either a full or part time position but not bank at this time. For internal staff 12 month secondments are also available.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;By joining us in return we offer competitive professional development packages including academic enhancement along with flexible working opportunities within a supportive working environment which challenges and rewards in equal measure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like to find out more information regarding the role you can contact clinicalteamleadersnorth@swast.nhs.uk for Bristol or clinicalteamleaderssouth@swast.nhs.uk for Exeter for an informal conversation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are welcomed and would be encouraged to arrange a visit to our Clinical Hubs and can do so by contacting the above.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(*) Paid under Section 2 of NHS Terms and Conditions. Please see A4C Handbook attached to advert.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
